5<//rating>
<Text>As a former graduate of NU Fresno Campus (2002) BS IT, I decided to attend an orientation for the EMT Program based on a notification. I was considering a career change and I definitely do not regret committing to this program. The instructors are all seasoned Paramedic Professionals and there is a lot of attention to hands on skills based learning. I will be going on my first ride along to experience an actual shift of EMT work. I recommend this program if you are interested in committing to a thorough and fast paced team oriented learning style.< /Text>< Pictures>

< review>
I am currently enrolled in the EMT program at National University, Fresno. I am thoroughly enjoying it. The instructors are very knowledgeable in the field, have tons of field experience, and are competent to teach. The only reason I didn't rate it fulls stars, is because this is the first time these instructors have not worked together. They are not all on the same  page. and I feel like they could prepare a little more for their lectures. This however will improve(they have already improved) as this Fresno program continues. I am learning tons, and feel like I will be able to pass the class.</review>

<Text>EMT program is amazing.  It is organized, comprehensive, straight-forward, challenging, fun, and some.  Coming in as a Registered Nurse, I was able to listen to other view points and learn different techniques.  I feel is very valuable.  The information taught was explained clearly and thoroughly, and time was taken for others until understood.  We all learned as a team and grew together as a class.  Our instructors helped build our confidence while also improving our leadership skills in command presence.  I appreciate them, and I suggest this course to others.  Worth it.< /Text><pics>None< /pics>< resp>

I am currently enrolled in the EMT program at National University, Fresno. I am thoroughly enjoying it. <rate>5< /rate>< Review>
EMT program is amazing.  It is organized, comprehensive, straight-forward, challenging, fun, and some.  Coming in as a Registered Nurse, I was able to listen to other view points and learn different techniques.  I feel is very valuable.  The information taught was explained clearly and thoroughly, and time was taken for others until understood.  We all learned as a team and grew together as a class.  Our instructors helped build our confidence while also improving our leadership skills in command presence.  I appreciate them, and I suggest this course to others.  Worth it.< /Review>

< Review>
I wanted to express how much I love living at the Summit! The staff here has really gone above and beyond during the pandemic to still make sure that we are taken care of.  I moved in about three months ago and I could not be happier with my home.  Kami helped me find the perfect location and floorplan to fit all of my needs and checked off all of the boxes I was looking for. There are a lot of newer buildings in the area, but none of the staff at those buildings made me feel more welcome than her.  I also have had great service from Sonia, Carol, and Joysmeri in Resident Services.  They are always happy to assist whenever I have had a work order.  It really feels like the whole staff cares about the residents.  The maintenance techs always smile and wave as I walk around the community.  They even try to make holidays special by offering treats to the residents, and they just started having Food Trucks come weekly which has been a great way to meet neighbors.  I’m glad I chose the Summit over all of the other places I was looking at.  It really feels like a home, and my family and I couldn’t be happier!< /Review>

<review>It's not perfect but it's not as bad as other seem to make it.

It's a beautiful community, everyone is very friendly, and I have never had an issue with getting something fixed in my unit.

The price is high but for the area, it's actually pretty competitive considering the washer/drier in every unit and attached 2 car garage. I couldn't find anything in the safety of the West Valley that offers a Townhouse style living situation for a better price.

It's walking distance from movie theaters, malls and restaurants as well.

We have been there for a year while we shop for a house and so far we've been very happy.

EDIT: Dropping a star because of the huge price increase. We were paying $100 per month more every year but this year it almost went up $300 per month. WAY too expensive for what you get and the poor maintenance and customer service.

<Review>Do not be fooled by the website. This place is god awful. I have lived here for 2 years and the window dressing on the show apartments are just that. I couldn't figure out how to arrange my rant so the problems below are in no particular order:

1. Security. Technically this is a gated community. Yes there are gates and when you sign the lease you are required to list your common visitors so they can be let in without security calling you. The problem is they let everyone in. The security guard, although be it nice, just asks what address you are visiting. They write up a sheet of paper (which no copy is made) and then they send each visitor on their marry way. Additionally, at least 1 gate is always broken and left wide open.

2. Customer Service. The Leasing office is beautiful. The staff are useless. They are usually too busy gossiping or eating to give you their full attention.

3. Maintenance. If you want something fixed don't fill out the on-line request because it dies a slow death in a black hole until you call and speak to a Customer Service Rep in the front office (see #2). Last winter it took them 3 weeks to fix the heat because the maintenance tech who works on heat was on vacation. In lieu of calling a vendor was to provide a tiny space heater, which I had to sign for just in case it was lost so they could charge me for it. Another example, all my showers were leaking, couldn't tighten them enough. I had to request they be fixed 3 times before they actually stopped leaking.

4. The Apartment. I have a 3 bedroom apartment that has been "Upgraded". Let me translate what that means. 1. cheap marble counters in the bathrooms and kitchen, that have holes in them and are not properly sealed. 2. Cabinets from 1980 that have 30 coats of paint. The top coat is this dark chocolate brown that when it chips has yellowy-white paint underneath. Also the entire cabinet is not painted, just the faces. The heating/cooling units are the original ones from when the unit were built in the 70/80's. They are loud and don't work very well. For the first 3 months (in the summer) we called the Maintenance group once a week to check on them until the maintenance tech let me know they were old and never going to work the way I wanted. I appreciated his honestly, but I still upset about the situation.< /Review><Date>1414022685889<//Date></record></dataset><record>

<text>ZERO STARS IF POSSIBLE. Read before you lease. Proceed with caution!
They will try to scam you! They never give refunds!
The new management is WORSE THAN THE OLD ONE.

DO NOT LEASE WITH ICON PLAZA.
-	You are only allowed to have guests over for three consecutive days a week, three times a month. Anywhere else, you can have people over anytime and as long as you want.
-	Move-in date is always the last 2 weeks of AUGUST, you MUST PAY IN FULL. This means you are NOT PRO-RATED and they rationalize this by “giving” you 8 “free days in August” which does NOT ADD UP TO ONE MONTH. (The next two bullet-points are related).
-	You are REQUIRED to WAIT FIVE DAYS BEFORE MOVE IN, WHICH MEANS YOU WON’T EVEN BE LIVING AT ICON FOR FIVE DAYS YOU PAID FOR. Wait, the next one is a kicker.
-	You are REQUIRED to MOVE OUT FIVE DAYS BEFORE, WHICH MEANS YOU WON’T BE LIVING for those FIVE DAYS YOU PAID FOR. That’s a grand total of 10 days out of a month. Which means you’re ultimately paying almost TWO GRAND for TE…EIGHT DAYS.
-	Rent is extremely expensive for a very miniature room. I am under 5 foot tall and I repeatedly bump my knee on the bed every night.
-	They will charge you for lock outs ($35 for business hours, and $75 for after-hours)
-	You cannot go up to your unit unless you have a fob key. There are only TWO ELEVATORS. Parents, good luck reaching your kids here. Especially when parking is terrible, they tow you if you use the parking, and without a key.
-	You are not allowed to check out the room you will be leasing. You go in blind on the first day to see a smaller room than anticipated with a dirty bed.
-	There are bed-bugs, my legs are full of scars from them (pictures attached).
-	You will be charged for utilities, and if you do not switch your accounts, they will charge you $50 on top of other fees, regardless if you ALREADY DID IT AND THE COMPANY MADE A MISTAKE. They will not take this charge out of your bill.
-	Rent is always increasing.
-	Never ever take a refund from ICON. Trust me, they will probably hand you a gift card just like they did for me.
-	Furniture, appliances are broken long before you enter. They still make you pay for it!
-	Subleasing is IMPOSSIBLE. You are required to pay $250 fee, your sub-leaser is required to pay a DEPOSIT of $250. IF YOUR SUB-LEASER DOES NOT PAY HIS/HER RENT, YOU ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS AMOUNT EVEN IF THEY LIVE THERE CURRENTLY AND YOU ARE NOT. For the love of god, do not sign a lease with these people!
-	At other places, like USC-operated housing, you are able to get out of a lease if you can prove that you are leaving for an internship. At ICON, it is impossible, you will be stuck with this lease.
-	Some of the student workers are okay, but man that book-keeper lady is ruthless, terrible, and rude to one of my roommates when all of us were charged $80 for a billing mistake with NO REFUNDS.</text><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP_gmrsSdWEBiltcABCSNifKJNuQ7QWFoLKu7w-=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOJ9k971eKx5bedFZAVWeSUV5GoXGbFdpqzUOSD=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pictures></record>

<Rate>5</Rate><review>I've been living here for 4 years now, and Icon Plaza is by far the best option for student housing! The manager Nicole and Helena are always so patient with my needs and concerns. They always go above and beyond to fix any issues and respond to emails so quickly! They are such caring people who always take the time to understand and address your needs. Also, the amenities here are absolutely amazing with free printing (in a 24 hr study room), a pool, a 24 hr gym, and a game room. Of course, due to COVID, these are currently closed, but before COVID I utilized every single one of these and it has made my life so much easier. If it weren't for Icon Plaza, my college housing experience would've been stressful and horrible. The place is so clean and safe as I've never had a package stolen. Even my friends not living in Icon have their packages delivered to me to avoid dealing with package thieves in their living area. The rent can be slightly pricey, but for the cleanliness, attentiveness of the staff, and safe location, it's definitely worth every penny. I have no problem paying rent because I feel like I've saved so much time not having to walk to the gyms and study lounges on campus! I also love how the leases are individual! I am so blessed to have found this place. The people in the office spread so much positivity and happiness, and they really do care so much about each individual resident. Literally, every suite mate I have ever lived with here has loved this place so much and wished they hadn't wasted their time with other housing places around USC.</review>< Pics>

<username>Jordan Reilly<//username><Time>1537493391216<//Time><rating>1<//rating>< review>
I lived in Icon Plaza for two years and loved it my first year and loved it less my second year. I have always appreciated the amenities, the proximity to campus and the student and maintenance staff members who work in Icon. This past May, new management "Greystar" bought the building and laid off many staff members. They charged me an extra $200 dollars a month for "late fees" and threatened to evict me three times for not paying rent. I encourage current and future tenants to keep track of their payments and keep their receipts so they have proof that they paid on time. Additionally, after I moved out, they charged me an extra $273 to repaint and clean the entire apartment and for a broken desk. Having not put anything up on the walls and having not broken my desk, I asked for proof in pictures that I had inflicted any damage on the apartment. They were unable to provide me evidence, but insisted that my roommates and I had cause over $900 of damage to our apartment. In summary, I would caution anyone and everyone when looking into living at Icon. I would never recommend it to anyone, not because of the living conditions or the amenities, but because of the rude management and their tendency to overcharge and create false damage charges.

I've already talked with management (so don't bother commenting with your phone number) and their BS is just the same as always. I wish I'd made the leap to move out years ago and I hope others don't fall into the trap. Shout out to Amanda, a student worker, who was the only one in the entire place who was nice and amazingly helpful. The only redeeming quality of Icon.

Oh, and FYI, they used to give us $10 gift cards if we posted 5 star reviews.</review>

This place was nice when I moved here a year ago, but unfortunately has been completely ruined by the new management and certain staff members, particularly Alex.

Alex is the bookkeeper, which is terrible news considering that’s who you have to pay rent to. 1614185181147<//Time>
< Rating>
2<//Rating>
<text>Our experience with Tracy VW started off well, then deteriorated as time went by.

The Good
Found a 2017 Escalade for a decent price. The vehicle itself has been great. No problems mechanically in the two months we have owned it. Came with a broken third brake light (don’t know how we missed that), but I can change that on my own. Still a decent deal. Came with ‘lifetime powertrain warranty’. It looks nice on paper but a warranty is only as good as the dealership willing to honor it. Only time will tell.

The Bad
We were told a certain price for our trade-in before we showed up. During the deal, they tried sneaking in a lower amount. Luckily, I caught that and had it changed. They also told us we could get a ‘bumper to bumper’ warranty with a $100 deductible. We did not pay attention during the paperwork signing (it was late night), and we later found they had bumped up the ‘deductible’ to $200. We had also specifically asked them to use Safe CU because we were approved by them. They ended up using Capital One (and a higher rate than Safe) and now we have to refinance this loan. A few weeks after the deal, I decided to go over the paperwork carefully and found they has added the Express Portfolio coverages without really explaining what it was ($3000 worth). So we messaged Abid (Finance guy- ughhh) and he said he would cancel it that day (Jan 17).

The Ugly
We found out, after reading the extended service contract, that the ‘wrap’ coverage we paid for covers most things EXCEPT the powertrain. Granted that the dealer gave us a powertrain coverage from them, but their explanation (that the extended contract would cover bumper to bumper) was very misleading. Also, I called Express Portfolio on 2/22/2021 to see when we would get our refund credited to our loan so we could refinance, and they said THE DEALER HAD NOT EVEN SUBMITTED A CANCELLATION YET. I had to jump through hoops to try to have them cancel it and hopefully that goes through. Of course, just like even finance person, Abid has been very unresponsive regarding this. It has been six weeks since my request, and nothing has been done yet. I will wait a few weeks before going to BBB and DCA. If these guys are taking my being nice and polite as being naive and foolish, they are mistaken. This aint my first rodeo.

Overall, they are no different than any other dealer. Be careful, be stern, and comb through the paperwork before signing it. My fault for being so trusting and nice. These folks are sneaky. If you get a great deal, take it with caution. I am not doing business with them again. Hopefully they honor my lifetime powertrain warranty should I ever need it, otherwise BAR, here I come!!< /text>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>

< text>
I bought my first car, a 2015 VW Jetta, from a dealership in Stockton. Throughout the two years that followed, any time i needed it serviced i brought it to Tracy Volkswagen. The guys always did a great job; working quickly and keeping me updated, along with being friendly and easy going. Later on i’d receive calls from the dealership claiming they liked the condition of my car and were interested in trading it in. I wasn’t sure at first, though they persisted and eventually convinced me to come in for a quick appraisal. I had an appointment set up for a Tuesday, but the Friday before i got a call from a guy named Jericho who said he could fit me in during the weekend. So i came in, figuring i’d just take a look around, somewhat skeptically. He took me around the lot, showing me some nice cars and answering all my questions and more in great detail. I said i wasn’t sure if i could afford the car that i ended up falling in love with, and he said let’s go inside and go over the numbers, and “let me work for you”. so we went inside and he fought to get me the payment i desired, going back and forth to the boss to get it done. next thing i knew i was leaving the dealership in my beautiful, brand new Jetta, leaving behind my older reliable but sketchy car. Completely made my day. Whole process took 2 hours or less. i even forgot my $300 glasses in the old car and Jericho saved them for me—fantastic job !!<//text>

<review>From my experience this is no typical car dealer.
I recently bought  a used 2017 VW Jetta  from Tracy VW and I was treated very well throughout every phase of the purchase. Michael Liu was my sales Rep. and he helped me with every step of the process. It was very important to Michael that I understood all my options and was happy from start to finish.
Buying a used car is usually a very stressful experience for me but Michael did everything in his power to make the process as painless as possible.
My happiness and satisfaction seems to be Michael's top priority.
I had selected the car  I was interested in from their website before I arrived and Michael did not try to up-sell or pressure me into buying something else,
He simply wanted to show me the car and make sure all my questions were answered to my satisfaction.
Of course, no used vehicle is perfect but
Michael answered all my questions honestly and openly about any imperfection I found. The windshield had a small crack and Michael assured me that it would be taken care of.
As with many people, I needed to finance the car and again, Michael explained my options, answered all my questions and presented me with several choices to best fit my needs and circumstances. I swear, Michael was as happy as I was when we found that I was eligible for a better rate and terms than  we had expected.
This was due to Patrick Connelly (General Manager)  expertly arranging the financing. Patrick went to great length to get me the best rate possible.
Now, buying a used car is a lengthy process and it takes like 6-8 hours start to finish but the staff at Tracy VW do their best to ensure that their customers are as comfortable as possible throughout the entire experience.
So, I bought the car and Michael got the new windshield on order and after a couple of weeks, when the new windshield arrived, I got the call to bring the car in for a free replacement. YEA !
I feel that it is important to note that Michael never promised anything that be did not follow through with.
This kind of honesty and integrity is very refreshing
In today's environment where many people are only interested in making a quick buck.
I would not hesitate to recomend to anyone who needs a good, reliable, vehicle from an excellent dealership to visit Tracy VW.
Thanks again to Michael Liu and Patrick Connelly for making my used car buying experience special from start to finish.< /review><gmap_id>0x8090180d971682b9:0x3c0e488b3bd0e97b<//gmap_id>< pics>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< text>
This was, by far, my best car buying experience.
Volkswagen has huge discounts this April ($6,400 off MSRP) and I wanted to take advantage and buy a new Passat. I leave in Sacramento and, naturally, I first checked the offers from the local dealers (Roseville, Folsom Lake, Niello and Elk Grove). I asked them for their best offers and did not find any of them enticing, let alone that some of them did not have the color combinations that were my first 2 options. I decided to search all dealers on a 100 miles radius. I noticed that Tracy VW had the highest discount $6,500) posted on their website. I made a phone call to Tracy VW and spoke to Andy Barrios. After explaining what I wanted and what the best offers were so far, he promised to e-mail me an offer. I received an e-mail 15 minutes later and his offer was absolutely the best for the exact color combination that I wanted. I agreed to buy the car and Kyle Sweet e-mailed me the financing application to save time at the dealership. It took about an hour to finish all the paperwork and drive happy with my brand new Passat.
Andy and Kyle exceed my wildest expectations. No haggling, no stalling, no bait and switch, no additional pricey options and so forth. Straight to the best offer and that was it. This is how car buying should be.
Thank you guys. You rock. I will send your way all my friends and colleagues who are looking to buy a VW.<//text>

<UserId.>102519533121975459148<//UserId.><Name>Jason Norman</Name><Time>1616941225146</Time><rate>1< /rate>< Text>
Good beer, but why is it twice the price to sit down and enjoy a beer from a pint glass than to buy it from the front in a pint sized can? I went there today and had two beers with a buddy. They were great. So when it was time to leave I grabbed a 4 pack of pints and it was the same amount as the two pours so from now on I’ll be enjoying that little hack instead of getting ripped off by the establishment. ;)

Update after reading Vic’s response:
Don’t be weird Vic, I gave an honest review of your business model and how I will interact with it in the future. As a business owner just hear the review and consider it in the future when making your business decisions. Don’t make it personal like you have today.<//Text>
<pics>None< /pics><resp>{'time': 1616907198877, 'text': 'Hi Jason,\n\nThanks for your review Jason,  as many businesses have closed recently and others are struggling to survive through the pandemic, we appreciate every bit of negative vibes we receive.  Your accusation of us ripping you off, just further pile on the awful events from this past year.  Thank you for kicking us while we are down with the 2 star review.\n\nWe are glad you enjoyed the beer, as our employees work countless hours to perfect their craft and do their best to create the best beer possible.  However, if you are just looking at dollars and cents, you are somewhat correct in your assumption that draft beer costs more than the canned beers, however, the pints are 20oz UK pints served on draft and the cans are 16oz pints. So your math is a little off...    Almost any other "establishment" will charge more than we do for a 16oz pint.\n\nJason, you are also not considering quality vs. quantity.  Draft beer is the pinnacle of quality for a beer.  It is the freshest and most true to form medium for beer to be enjoyed. Canning is definitely sub-par to draft, as any canning of beer will degrade the flavor and quality of the beer due to a variety of factors.  Even the Macro "establishment" breweries like Budweiser beer is not the same out of a can. So, Jason, in fact you are not comparing the same thing.  In addition, a pint of "Bud" in a bar ranges from $5-$9 and the cans sell in the stores for about $1.50 each.\n\nFinally, you are viewing this the wrong way....Instead of thinking of this family owed business as an "establishment" ripping you off, you should be thinking that you got a great deal on a 4-pack of cans and give us a 5-star review for our amazing beer and prices.  If you like, we can raise the prices of our cans so that no one gets a deal at all, and it will be all thanks to you bringing it to our attention. We look forward to the change of your review to a 5-star review.\n\nThanks,\nVic'}</resp><gmap_id>0x80c291b6eddaad91:0xb1dcdf89db38dc9e< /gmap_id></record>

< Review>
Located in the heart of San Fernando Valley, this award winning brewery surely brings delicious beer into your palate. Place seems small from the outside but it's actually huge inside. Must try their award winning O'melveny Red Ale, 7.5% ABV, 21 IBUs. They can also make any beer into a michelada. You can also enjoy their free popcorn and pretzels. Friendly staff, props to sexy Marissa :-)<//Review>

Great brewery with a spacious tap room and a very relaxed, family-friendly atmosphere.  OK selection of brews.  The stout is outstanding, many others are good, the lighter ones are a little too light in my opinion.  Beers are a bit much at $8, but they do have free prertzels and popcorn to offset that. <Resp>None</Resp><Time>1569604422934</Time><text>Reasons as to why this brewery is memorable for me
- Fast and friendly service: The staff cared about what we like to drink and gave us some suggestions and samples first thing
- Beers here were very interesting and there was a variety. If you're into IPAs, they have a few with some fruity ones like a Grapefruit IPA to a triple IPA. I really enjoyed the Wolfskill one! In general, you can really taste the flavor of the beers. For example, you'd think that the grapefruit ipa would just have a subtle hint of grapefruit like many citra and mosaic IPAs, but you could smell the grapefruit before you drink it! They had a cucumber lager and pumpkin pie ale. My tastebuds were honestly overwhelmed, but also very amazed!
- Free popcorn and pretzels
- Spacious place with lots of board games and wifi!< /text></record>

< Review>
Super good!!! I've heard of this place here and there but finally got around to trying it. I came here with two Texans who are very not Asian, but they both loved it! It's definitely a good place for everyone, in my opinion.

We ordered two things:
#4 - Traditional beef noodles with Chinese pickle. I specifically requested no cilantro, but they gave me a soup with cilantro. When I brought this up to the waitress, she took the soup back to fix the mistake. I thought they would do kind of a best-effort removal of the cilantro, but I think they ended up remaking the entire dish. Either that, or they did a PHENOMENAL job removing them because I couldn't find a single trace of cilantro in the bowl she brought back.

#6 - Beef noodles with green & red chili peppers. The two Texans shared this dish and they loved it. I think they were caught off guard with the spiciness, but they finished this it regardless and were very happy with their meal.

Oh, also the portions are HUGE so maybe keep that in mind or find someone to share with.< /Review>

<Rating>4</Rating>< Review>
Noodology is such a warm and welcoming place to be at. However, their main courses are very unique and include a numbing spice that numbs up your tongue and throat. There are dishes without them, but before entering just be aware of these type of dishes that include spices. In my opinion I disliked the spices because I have an allergy (most dishes include peanuts), and it felt like I was having a reaction even though it was just a mimic of it. The noodles are fresh and you have many different choices to your taste so enjoy as you'd like.</Review>

<Name>D Hndz< /Name><rating>2< /rating><Time>1525648617808</Time><userid>116615379659368760758<//userid>< Text>
Ambiance :

Music was painfully loud and Im used to loud . They had a mariachi which I love but their speakers were blasting  to try to cover the music from their small bar in the next room. The bar was louder than any night club and it was just a very uncomfortable experience.  I walked out with a headache.

Food:

Mediocre .  They serves in big plates that are mainly 95% rice and beans.  The food is nothing  special and overpriced.  We had Shirmp al mojo de ajo and  it was undercooked and they used garlic seasoning instead of real garlic (8 small shrimps. I counted them). We ordered salad instead of rice and beans and don't have a single homemade dressing. The spicy  salsa was basically canned chipotle  chillies with some seasoning.  The bacon wrapped shrimp was okay... bacon was a little burned . The taquitos were okay and enchilada was just okay. Margaritas tasted like a lemonade kool-aid.

This place has so much potential the place it's really nice and  they have good menu but they lack  good chef and good management.< /Text>

The favorite item for me at this restaurant are the out of this world homemade flour tortillas.  Order some if you get the chance.   This place is large and well appointed.  The bar is separated from the dining area and features live music on some nights.  Since it was late when we arrived we shared some appetizers.
